<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-09-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-09-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="380" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d380">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">de Margerie</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-09-30"><hi rend="italic">September 30,
                                    1902</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 509.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 25th instant, expressing anew the thanks of
                            the Government of <pb facs="0497" n="417" xml:id="pg_417"/> the French
                            Republic for the aid extended by the United States to the sufferers in
                            the recent volcanic eruption of Mont Pélée.</p>
                        <p>It was with gratification that I made this known to the Secretary of the
                            Navy.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>